AD_ELEMENT.NAME: User Name Attribute
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: User name attribute obtained from the OAuth2 provider. This field specifies which of the attributes from the OAuth2 provider's response should be used as the username in your application.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Provide the name of the attribute that should be used as the username in your application. This attribute is extracted from the OAuth2 provider's response after the user authenticates. Commonly used attributes are 'sub' (subject), 'email', or 'preferred_username'.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Client Name
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Name of the provider.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Here you can fill this field with a name or description about how do you want to call the provider.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: oAuth Provider
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: OAuth2 provider that handles authorization and authentication. An OAuth2 provider can be a service like Google, GitHub, Facebook, etc., which allows users to authenticate in your application using their existing credentials from that service.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Select the OAuth2 provider your application will use for authentication and authorization. This provider will be responsible for authenticating users and issuing access tokens. Common examples include Google, GitHub, and Facebook. Make sure you have registered your application with the selected provider and have the necessary credentials (Client ID and Client Secret).

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Client Authentication Method
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Client authentication method, e.g., basic, post, etc.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Specify the client authentication method. Common methods are 'basic' and 'post'. 'Basic' sends the credentials in the HTTP header, while 'post' sends them in the request body.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Token URI
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: URL to which requests are sent to obtain the access token.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Enter the token URL of the OAuth2 provider. This URL is used to exchange the authorization code for an access token.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Service URL
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: URL of the service.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Describe the URL of a service running on the instance.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Valid Until
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Token expiration date
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Describe the validity duration of the token

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Scope
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Scopes (permissions) that the application requests.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Specify the scopes that your application needs from the OAuth2 provider. These define the permissions your application is requesting, such as access to the user's profile or email.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Related Tabs
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This selector allows users to select specific tabs that are related to the current record's table.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: To use the Related Tab Selector field, click on it to view a list of available tabs associated with the current recordâ€™s table. Select the tab you want, and it will be linked to the record. Only tabs related to the table in use will be shown

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: OpenAPI Request
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: OpenAPI related request.
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Request related called when OpenAPI is called.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Authorization Grant Type
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Authorization grant type that defines how the application obtains the access token from the OAuth2 provider. Common examples include authorization_code, implicit, password, and client_credentials.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Select the authorization grant type your application will use to obtain access tokens. The most common types are 'authorization_code' (uses an authorization code), 'implicit' (without authorization code), 'password' (uses user credentials), and 'client_credentials' (uses client credentials).

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Entity Mapping
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The Entity Mapping field defines the relationship between a resource and its corresponding entity within the system, linking the endpoint to its data model.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Specify the entity that this endpoint interacts with. This mapping helps connect the web service path to the appropriate data model or resource within the system.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Authorization URI
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: URL to which authorization requests are sent to obtain user consent.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Provide the authorization URL of the OAuth2 provider. This URL is used to redirect users to log in and grant permissions to your application.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: OpenAPI Tab
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Tabs that are displayed in the OpenAPI window.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Selected tab in current request

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: GET Token
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Button to execute the process the retrieve a token from a provider.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This process establish the communication with the provider in order to get and create a new token.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: User Info URI
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: URL from which authenticated user details are obtained.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Provide the user info URL of the OAuth2 provider. This URL is used to get the profile data of the authenticated user.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Authorization Endpoint
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This field specifies the URL where users go to give permission for an app to access their data. It's the starting point for apps to get approval to access user information.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: When a user wants to use an app that requires access to their data (like signing in with Google or Facebook), they're sent to this URI. Here, they log in and decide if they want to allow the app to access their information. After permission is granted, they're sent back to the app with a special code that lets the app access their data.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Path Management
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This field stores the endpoint path used to manage specific resources in the RESTful web service.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Enter the path used for managing resources via the RESTful service. This path defines where the specific resource operations (e.g., GET, POST, PUT) are performed.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Updateable Configs
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Check to declare if the service can refresh it's configs.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: By enabling this check, the 'Refresh Config' process will update the configs related to this service if they were changed.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Method name
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The name of the method related to a query

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Redirect URI
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: URL to which the OAuth2 provider redirects after user consent.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Enter the 'Redirect URI' your application will use to receive the OAuth2 response. This URI must match the one configured in the OAuth2 provider.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: RX Config
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Configs of Etendo RX
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Configs of Etendo RX

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Is RX
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Etendo RX module

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Refresh Configs
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Button to execute the process that refresh the oAuth Provider configs.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: This button execute a process that, after saving news or updated configs, will refresh the services that has the 'Updateable Configs' flag checked on RX Config windows.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Service Name
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Name of the services.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Describes the name of a services on the instance.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Code Challenge Method
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Code challenge method used in the authorization code flow to enhance security. This is part of PKCE (Proof Key for Code Exchange). Common methods include plain and S256.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Specify the code challenge method your application will use. This is used in the authorization flow to increase security. Common methods are 'plain' (no encryption) and 'S256' (SHA-256). We recommend 'S256' for enhanced security.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: HTTP Method
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: This field stores the HTTP method used to define the action performed on the resource in the RESTful web service.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Select the HTTP method (e.g., GET, POST, PUT, DELETE) that determines the type of operation to execute on the resource associated with the endpoint.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: oAuth API URL
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Store the API URL
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: API URL to reach the provider. It can be found on https://market.apis-i.redsys.es/psd2/xs2a/nodos/{provider-name}

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: ID for Client
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: Unique identifier provided by the OAuth2 provider when you register your application.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Enter the 'Client ID' you received when registering your application with the OAuth2 provider (e.g., Google, GitHub). This is a unique identifier for your application.

AD_ELEMENT.NAME: Path
AD_ELEMENT.DESCRIPTION: The Path field specifies the endpoint's URL path used to access or interact with a resource in the RESTful web service.
AD_ELEMENT.HELP: Enter the specific URL path that identifies the resource within the web service. This path is appended to the base URL to direct requests to the correct resource.
